-- Polenergia Would Bid for Enea, Energa, Rzeczpospolita Reports
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-09-25T05:42:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/polenergia-would-bid-for-enea-energa-rzeczpospolita-reports.html
Polenergia Holding, a unit of
Kulczyk Investments, would be “a natural investor” for  Enea SA (ENA) 
and Energa SA, Kulczyk’s Chief Executive Officer Dariusz Mioduski said in an interview with Rzeczpospolita newspaper.  Polenergia would consider bidding for stakes in the Polish
state-controlled utilities when the government offers them for
sale, the newspaper quoted Mioduski as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  